Schalk Coetzee (Facebook via Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein &ndash; The family of a Bloemfontein quantity surveyor, who is believed to have drowned after his body was found in a jacuzzi on Tuesday morning, is shattered by his death, Netwerk24 reported.It is believed that Schalk Coetzee, 45, drowned between 04:00 and 04:45, possibly after falling asleep in the jacuzzi on a farm in the Verkeerdevlei district.Coetzee was a surveyor and manager at Razzmatazz Plant Civil Works in Bloemfontein.He'd earlier had friends over to the farm.His body was found by a cleaner at about 08:50 on Tuesday morning and paramedics were unable to resuscitate him.Members of the Brandfort community described Coetzee as a good father.A friend, Awie Nel, said Coetzee's wife Karen and their three children, Rouxl&eacute;, Nerike and Melinda, were devastated by his sudden death.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.